<div class=3D"container" id=3D"content">
    <h1>md5 Hash Generator</h1>
    <blockquote><p>This simple tool computes the MD5 hash of a string. Also=
 available: <a href=3D"https://www.miraclesalad.com/webtools/sha1.php">SHA-=
1 hash generator</a> and <a href=3D"https://www.miraclesalad.com/webtools/s=
ha256.php">SHA-256 hash generator</a>.</p></blockquote>

    <form action=3D"https://www.miraclesalad.com/webtools/md5.php" method=
=3D"post" id=3D"form">
        <div id=3D"group1" class=3D"group">
            <h2><label for=3D"string">String(s):</label> <button type=3D"re=
set" class=3D"btn btn-small btn-outline-primary">=C3=97 Clear</button></h2>
            <p>
                <textarea name=3D"string" cols=3D"50" rows=3D"5" id=3D"stri=
ng" autocapitalize=3D"off" class=3D"form-control" autofocus=3D""></textarea=
>
            </p>
            <p class=3D"d-flex gap-2 align-items-top">
                <button type=3D"submit" name=3D"Submit" class=3D"btn btn-pr=
imary" value=3D"md5">md5</button>
                <span>
                    <span class=3D"checkbox"><label><input type=3D"checkbox=
" name=3D"multiline" id=3D"multiline" class=3D"checkbox" value=3D"1"> Treat=
 multiple lines as separate strings</label> (blank lines are ignored)</span=
><br>
                    <span class=3D"checkbox"><label><input type=3D"checkbox=
" name=3D"uppercase" id=3D"uppercase" class=3D"checkbox" value=3D"1"> Upper=
case hash(es)</label></span><br>
                    <span class=3D"checkbox"><label><input type=3D"checkbox=
" name=3D"blur" id=3D"blur" class=3D"checkbox" value=3D"1"> Blur string(s)<=
/label></span>
                </span>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div id=3D"group2" class=3D"group">
            <h2>
                <label for=3D"output">MD5 Hash(es):</label>
                <button type=3D"button" class=3D"btn btn-sm btn-outline-pri=
mary copy-to-clipboard float-end" data-clipboard-target=3D"#output"><svg wi=
dth=3D"1em" height=3D"1em" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" class=3D"svg-icon md-copy-=
content" aria-hidden=3D"true" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d=
=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path><path d=3D"M16 1H4c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v=
14h2V3h12V1zm3 4H8c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h11c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V7c0-1=
.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 16H8V7h11v14z"></path></svg>
 <span>Copy to clipboard</span></button>
            </h2>
            <p>
                <textarea name=3D"output" id=3D"output" class=3D"form-contr=
ol" rows=3D"1"></textarea>
            </p>
        </div>
    </form>
    <p><strong>Privacy notice:</strong> All content generated by this tool =
is done on your computer via client-side JavaScript whenever possible, or o=
n the Miracle Salad server as a fallback if not. No submitted or generated =
data is recorded or stored by Miracle Salad. See the <a href=3D"https://www=
.miraclesalad.com/privacy.php">website privacy statement</a> regarding gene=
ral use of this website.</p>
    <p><mark>Special note about line endings:</mark> Mac/Unix and Windows u=
se different codes to separate lines. <strong>The tool on this page normali=
zes all line endings to a Line Feed (<code>\n</code>)</strong>. Other tools=
 are available online if you need hashes specifically with Windows line end=
ings (Carriage Return + Line Feed: <code>\r\n</code>).</p>
    <p><mark>Reminder:</mark> <a href=3D"http://www.mscs.dal.ca/~selinger/m=
d5collision/">MD5 is not a cryptographically secure hashing algorithm</a>.<=
/p>

